.TH "ima_read_file" 9 "ima_read_file" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
ima_read_file \- pre-measure/appraise hook decision based on policy
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" ima_read_file
.BI "(struct file *file "  ","
.BI "enum kernel_read_file_id read_id "  ","
.BI "bool contents "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "file" 12
pointer to the file to be measured/appraised/audit
.IP "read_id" 12
caller identifier
.IP "contents" 12
whether a subsequent call will be made to \fBima_post_read_file\fP
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Permit reading a file based on policy. The policy rules are written
in terms of the policy identifier.  Appraising the integrity of
a file requires a file descriptor.

For permission return 0, otherwise return -EACCES.
